President Trump expressed his sympathy for Paul Manafort, stating that he believes Manafort is a good man and expressing sadness about his situation. Trump also reiterated that the charges against Manafort have nothing to do with Russian collusion and called the investigation a "witch hunt" and a "disgrace". He emphasized that the original mission of the investigation was not to target Manafort, but it ended up that way. Trump concluded by stating that the investigation continues despite the lack of evidence of Russian involvement in his campaign.